# AutoDown Module

## Overview

AutoDown is the block-based rich-text editor for AutoForge. It is built on Tiptap/ProseMirror and uses Markdown as its serialization format, with Auto language-inspired extensions for table metadata and other structured content.

## Core Components

| Component | Path | Responsibility |
|---|---|---|
| `AutoDownEditor.vue` | `frontend/src/components/editors/autodown/core/AutoDownEditor.vue` | Main editor component, hosts Tiptap editor instance |
| `useAutoDownEditor` | `frontend/src/components/editors/autodown/composables/useAutoDownEditor.ts` | Editor initialization, IAL preprocessing, event wiring |
| `createExtensions` | `frontend/src/components/editors/autodown/extensions/index.ts` | Tiptap extension registry (StarterKit, Table, TaskList, etc.) |
| `tableAttributes` | `frontend/src/components/editors/autodown/extensions/tableAttributes.ts` | IAL parsing, generation, and ProseMirror attribute application |
| `rowResizing` | `frontend/src/components/editors/autodown/extensions/rowResizing.ts` | ProseMirror plugin for row-height drag resizing |
| `SlashMenu` | `frontend/src/components/editors/autodown/menus/SlashMenu.vue` | `/` command palette for block insertion |
| `BubbleMenu` | `frontend/src/components/editors/autodown/menus/BubbleMenu.vue` | Inline formatting toolbar on text selection |
| `TableMenu` | `frontend/src/components/editors/autodown/menus/TableMenu.vue` | Floating toolbar for table row/column operations |

## Architecture Relationship

- **Specs** — AutoDown is used in the Wiki page editor and may be used for inline spec editing
- **Wiki** — Primary consumer; WikiView embeds AutoDownEditor for page creation/editing
- **UiSystem** — Depends on theme CSS variables (`--af-border`, `--af-fg`, etc.)

